Hospital Admission Insight
The hospital admission dashboard highlights key trends in patient volume and demographics.
Admissions peaked significantly in 2018 with 74M patients, compared to 16M in 2017 and a drop to 35M in 2019,
suggesting a possible anomaly or surge in demand during 2018.
Monthly data shows a sharp decline in April (4.1M) followed by a steady recovery toward December (14M),
indicating potential seasonal or external factors affecting admissions.
The average patient age is relatively high at 61.43 years, implying a predominantly older population requiring care.
Outcomes are largely positive, with 87.3% of patients discharged, while mortality remains low. Gender distribution is fairly balanced,
though slightly male-dominated. Most patients fall within the middle-aged group (50.35%), highlighting a key demographic segment for healthcare services.
